==English==

===Etymology===
Popularized by the television show ''[[w:The Simpsons|The Simpsons]]'', specifically in the episode titled ''“[[w:Hungry Hungry Homer|Hungry Hungry Homer]]”'' (Season 12, Episode 15.)

===Interjection===
'''meh'''

# {{cattag|internet|slang}} An interjection expressing [[indifference]], [[apathy]], or “[[I don't know|I don’t know]]”; the verbal equivalent of a shrug of the shoulders.
#: ''“What do you want for dinner?” &mdash; “'''Meh'''.  I’m not really hungry.”''
#: ''“That film was awesome!” &mdash; “'''Meh'''.  I’ve seen better.”''
#: ''“How are you feeling today?” &mdash; “'''Meh'''...”''

